CM_ BO_ 422 "0x1A6 (DSC): Speed pulse counters for instrument cluster and time counter. SpeedCounter1/2/3 are duplicated speed pulse counters; TimeCounter increments by 100 every 50ms. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 436 "0x1B4 (CCC): Instrument cluster status — handbrake";
CM_ BO_ 437 "0x1B5 (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Heat flow climate";
CM_ BO_ 438 "0x1B6 (DME): Heat flow engine";
CM_ BO_ 450 "0x1C2 (PDC): Front and rear PDC sensor distances. RL/FL is furthest left, RR/FR is furthest right. Mid = inner sensors.";
CM_ BO_ 464 "0x1D0 (DME): Engine data — coolant temp, oil temp, idle target RPM";
CM_ BO_ 772 "0x304 (EGS): Current drive gear. B0=GearDisplay. Correlated with 0x1D2 ShiftLeverPosition: 0xE3=Park, 0xC2=Reverse, 0xD1=Neutral, 0xC1=Gear_1, 0xC5-0xC8=Gears 5-8. 0xC3=brief P->R transient (~320ms). B1=0xFF constant. Source: gearbox_modes.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 466 "0x1D2 (EGS): Transmission display data. ShiftLeverPosition HIL-validated: 1=P, 2=R, 4=N, 8=D. DS mode uses ShiftLeverMode=1(Sport). Actual drive gear while moving in 0x304 (Status_Gang). Source: clima_temp_fan.log HIL capture";
