CM_ BO_ 502 "0x1F6 (FRM — Footwell Module): Turn signal switch";
CM_ SG_ 502 HoldActivated "Spikes down if blinker cleared with timeout or turn. Stays off if blinker cleared with stalk";
CM_ SG_ 502 LeftTurn "Indicates left blinker or when steering returning left clears right blinker";
CM_ SG_ 502 RightTurn "Indicates right blinker or when steering returning right clears left blinker";
CM_ SG_ 502 TurnSignalActive "Turn signal on or transitioning";
CM_ SG_ 502 TurnSignalIdle "Turn signal off";
CM_ BO_ 514 "0x202 (FRM — Footwell Module): Dimming status";
CM_ BO_ 538 "0x21A (FRM — Footwell Module): Lighting and engine-running status. CORRECTION (keyless-restart log 2026-03-24): B0 bit7 is NOT KL15_Active — it is BRAKE_LIGHTS (brake pedal pressed). Evidence: bit7 clears to 0 immediately after start while engine is still running and KL15 is active (driver lifts foot off brake). The earlier correlation with ignition events was because diesel start requires brake pedal held, so brake-on and KL15-on events coincide. B0 bit0: reflects engine running state (1=engine running) but also correlates with dipped-beam (see full lighting decode). B0 bit2=SideLights. Confirmed B0 patterns: 0x04=sidelights_only (engine off, no brake), 0x84=brake+sidelights (brake pressed, engine off — restart prep), 0x85=brake+sidelights+engine_flag (cranking/just_started), 0x05=sidelights+engine_running_no_brake (normal driving), 0x05=also seen post-lock with engine on. B1=0x12 constant when KL15 active (from HIL-2). B2=0xF7 constant. [PARTIAL] Loopybunny exterior light decode (unconfirmed for this car): B0 lo-nibble: 0=all off, 4=sidelights/auto, 5=dip, 7=main. B1: 0=off, 1=reverse/tail, 16=interior, 18=interior+exterior. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC + HIL 2026-03-23 + keyless-restart 2026-03-24";
CM_ BO_ 550 "0x226 (FZD): Rain sensor and automatic wiper speed. B0=WiperActivity (0x00=off, 0x55=interval/active wiper mode set by rain sensor). B1=0xFE constant. B2=0xFF constant. B3=RainIntensity (0x00=no rain, 0x4F=rain detected — rises before wiper activates). B4=0xF3 constant. Source: 5ninutes_Full_Run_Cycle.log HIL capture (5 state changes observed with AUTO wiper in rain)";
CM_ BO_ 578 "0x242 (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Climate front status. B0 encodes recirc and special mode flags: bit0=always set, bit2=MaxACMode (0x05), bit4=RecircAuto (0x11), bit5=RecircManual (0x21). B1=0xF1 (0xF5 observed during defrost). B2 bit0=AC_Compressor_578 flag (0xFD=on, 0xFC=off). B3-B4=0xFF constant. Source: clima_modes_bottom_up.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 582 "0x246 (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Climate setpoint and AC status. B0=0x3F constant (purpose unknown). B1=0xF3 constant (purpose unknown). B2=TEMPERATURE SETPOINT (DBC signal ClimaTempSetpoint is CORRECT): formula raw*0.5+2.5 degC, range 0x1B-0x33 (16.0-28.0 degC). Validated at three setpoints in dedicated HIL capture 10minutes_run_temp_24_16_28_24.log 2026-03-24: 0x2B=24.0C, 0x1B=16.0C, 0x33=28.0C — all confirmed. Values 0x00=LO, 0x01-0x1A=below scale, 0x34+=HI (observed up to 0x3A when dial turned past maximum). B2=0x00 with AC-off seen at start/end of session (LO/AC-off state). NOTE: previous CM_ (HIL 2026-03-23) incorrectly identified B2 as a rolling counter — that analysis was from sessions with static setpoint and the apparent increment was coincidental. The original DBC signal name ClimaTempSetpoint was correct all along. B3=AC_Compressor flag: 0xFC=off, 0xFD=on (HIL-confirmed across multiple sessions). Source: 10minutes_run.log 2026-03-22 + HIL 2026-03-23 + HIL temp log 2026-03-24";
CM_ BO_ 678 "0x2A6 (SZL): Wiper mode switch from steering column. WiperSpeedMode nibble: 0=off, 1=interval_1, 2=interval_2, 3=slow. WiperAutoActive bit4: 0=off, 1=AUTO. B1=0xF9 constant. Source: wipers.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 690 "0x2B2 (DSC): Wheel pressure (TPMS)";
CM_ SG_ 691 Deceleration "Filtered deceleration. Opposite to AccY signal";
CM_ BO_ 691 "0x2B3 (DSC): Acceleration data";
CM_ BO_ 704 "0x2C0 (Kombi): LCD lighting / rear window heater status. B0 lo-nibble: 0x1F=normal, 0x3F=at startup (settling). B1: 0x00=normal, 0x81=rear-window-heater-active [HYPOTHESIS — HIL 2026-03-23: B1 changed 0x00→0x81 at t=327s during rear window heater test, stayed 0x81 until ignition-off — single session, needs confirmation with explicit on/off cycle]. B2=0x01 constant. Source: HIL 2026-03-23";
CM_ BO_ 758 "0x2F6 (FRM — Footwell Module): FZD interior ceiling light aggregate state. B0=FZD_InteriorState: 0x00=all_off, 0x01=courtesy_fade (single lamp, door just closed), 0x44=rear_on, 0x54=front_rear_on, 0x55=all_on_entry (door open / car entry). B1: 0xF5=initial/entry, 0xF0=running. Individual lamp bits unresolved. Source: FZD_Lights_right_to_Left_front_back.log + 5ninutes_Full_Run_Cycle.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 760 "0x2F8 (Kombi): System date and time";
CM_ SG_ 760 DateM "Top 4 bits only, lower nibble is always 0xF. eg: Jan=0x1F, May=0x5F, Dec=0xCF";
CM_ BO_ 762 "0x2FA (ACSM): Seat belt / occupancy. 5 bytes. B0 bit0=Occupancy_Driver [HYPOTHESIS: 0=not detected, 1=detected — set briefly at entry t=17s then stable from t=24s]. B1 bit0=Belt_Driver [HYPOTHESIS: 0=unbuckled, 1=buckled — 0x90→0x91 observed just before lock event at t=312s, consistent with driver unbuckling]. B2-B4=0xFF throughout (passenger seat empty in all captures). Only appears during KL15-on phase (event-triggered, ~5s interval during activity). Observed payloads: FC 04 FF FF FF (ECU wake), FD 91 FF FF FF (occupied+buckled), FC 90 FF FF FF (occupied, unbuckled?), FD 90 FF FF FF (stable seated). [HYPOTHESIS — single HIL session, needs dedicated belt buckle/unbuckle test to confirm bit mapping]. Source: HIL 2026-03-23 (10minutes_run_start_stop_most_HIL2_tests.log)";
CM_ BO_ 764 "0x2FC (CAS): Door and boot/bonnet open status. Byte 0 bitmask: b0=driver, b2=passenger, b4=rear-driver, b6=rear-passenger. Byte 2 bitmask: b0=boot, b2=bonnet. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 784 "0x310 (Kombi): Ambient temperature and relative time";
CM_ BO_ 790 "0x316 (Gate1): DTC push-button";
CM_ SG_ 790 DTC_pressed "Traction control off. Message transmitted when pressed. Few presses may be required followed by off.";
CM_ SG_ 790 setMe_0x3FFF "All ones";
CM_ BO_ 797 "0x31D (DSC): Tire pressure status";
CM_ BO_ 814 "0x328 (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Climate internal control info — light sensor (0-16 dash dimming), IR temp sensor, solar sensor. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 816 "0x330 (Kombi): Range / mileage (odometer)";
CM_ BO_ 821 "0x335 (EKP): Electric fuel pump status";
CM_ BO_ 823 "0x337 (DME): Fuel control status";
CM_ BO_ 841 "0x349 (Gate1): Raw fuel level sensor data (left and right tank floats)";
CM_ BO_ 842 "0x34A (CCC): GPS position — Longitude bytes 0-3 (32-bit signed, divide by 11930464.71 subtract 360 = degrees), Latitude bytes 4-7 (32-bit signed, divide by 11930464.71 = degrees). Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 847 "0x34F (Gate1): Handbrake lever contact. B0 bit0=Handbrake_pushed_down (1=lever down/released), B0 bit1=Handbrake_pulled_up (1=lever up/engaged). Exactly one bit active at a time. 0xFE=engaged, 0xFD=released. Validated across all HIL sessions: stationary sessions=0xFE, driving sessions=0xFD. Source: 5ninutes_Full_Run_Cycle.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 870 "0x366 (Kombi): External temperature and remaining fuel range. B0=ExternalTemp unsigned (factor=0.5, offset=-41 degC): formula raw*0.5-41. Validated: raw 0x6B=107 → 12.5C confirmed against dashboard at 12.5C ambient. B1-B2=FuelRange (miles). Source: STATIC-01 validation 2026-03-21";
CM_ BO_ 884 "0x374 (DSC): Wheel tolerance adjustment";
CM_ BO_ 896 "0x380 (CAS): Chassis / VIN number — bytes 0-6 are ASCII characters of VIN digits. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 897 "0x381 (DME): Engine oil level";
CM_ BO_ 940 "0x3AC (Gate1): Terminal 30 run-on time";
CM_ BO_ 944 "0x3B0 (FRM — Footwell Module): Reverse gear status. Byte 1: 0xFD=not in reverse, 0xFE=in reverse. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 945 "0x3B1 (DKG): Transmission data 3";
CM_ BO_ 947 "0x3B3 (DME): Power management consumption control";
CM_ BO_ 948 "0x3B4 (DME): Power battery voltage";
CM_ BO_ 958 "0x3BE (CAS): Power running time";
CM_ BO_ 1007 "0x3EF (DME): Engine OBD data";
CM_ BO_ 1554 "0x612 (DME): Diagnostic response";
CM_ BO_ 1632 "0x660 (Kombi): Diagnostic request acknowledgement";
CM_ BO_ 1777 "0x6F1 (DIA): Diagnostic request";
CM_ BO_ 417 "0x1A1 (XXX): Speed as used by instrument cluster. 5 bytes. Bytes 2-3 big-endian: ((B2*256)+B3)/100 = MPH. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 612 "0x264 (ZBE — iDrive Controller): iDrive controller rotary encoder. 6 bytes. Byte 2 = absolute position counter (0-254, increments per notch). Byte 3 = direction counter (0-254, up/down per rotation direction). Requires 0x273 activation. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 615 "0x267 (ZBE — iDrive Controller): iDrive controller buttons and joystick. 6 bytes. Bytes 0-1=E1 FD (static). Byte 2=counter. Byte 3 upper nibble=direction (1=up,2=right,4=down,8=left), lower nibble=press type (1=short,2=long). Byte 4=area (0xDE=menu/dir,0xDD=joystick,0xC0=multi). Byte 5=button bitmask. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 246 "0x0F6: Exterior mirror control / mirror position status. Sender: KGM (Body Gateway Module, node 0x00). 2-byte, static 0xF3 0xF3 in t1.log (idle/no-command state). Follows the body-module door-status +4 sequence: 0x0E2 BFT (passenger front door), 0x0E6 BFH (passenger rear door), 0x0EA FAT (driver front door), 0x0EE FAH (driver rear door), 0x0F2 HK (boot/tailgate), 0x0F6 mirrors. Source: MorGuux BMW E90 K-CAN gist. ** IMPORTANT: Mirror motor control on E90 goes via LIN bus (FRM Footwell Module -> LIN -> mirror motor actuators). The joystick input on K-CAN may trigger an FRM frame, but the actual mirror movement commands are LIN-bus-only and will NOT appear in a K-CAN capture. 0x0F6 = 0 frames confirmed in 10-min real drive log (10minutes_run.log) even though mirror adjustments were physically performed. K-CAN only sees 0xF3 0xF3 (idle/no-command state) periodically. To capture mirror commands: tap LIN bus at FRM connector, or read mirror position via UDS (0x7C3 FRM diagnostic frames observed at ts=76575-78642ms before vehicle movement may be position readout). **";
CM_ BO_ 494 "0x1EE (FRM — Footwell Module): Indicator / turn signal stalk position. Byte 0: 0=off, 1=up1st, 2=up2nd, 4=down1st, 8=down2nd, 16=full beam, 32=flash. Byte 1=0xFF. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 950 "0x3B6 (FRM — Footwell Module): FL (driver front) Window position feedback. WindowPosition(B0): 0=closed to 87=fully open. WindowMovement(B1): 0xFC=closed, 0xFD=moving, 0xFE=open. WindowMotionFlags(B2): motion state bits. HIL-validated from Windows_cycle.log";
CM_ BO_ 951 "0x3B7 (Gate1): RL (driver rear) Window position feedback. WindowPosition(B0): 0=closed to 87=fully open. WindowMovement(B1): 0xFC=closed, 0xFD=moving, 0xFE=open. WindowMotionFlags(B2): motion state bits. HIL-validated from Windows_cycle.log (limited data captured)";
CM_ BO_ 952 "0x3B8 (FRM — Footwell Module): FR (passenger front) Window position feedback. WindowPosition(B0): 0=closed to 87=fully open. WindowMovement(B1): 0xFC=closed, 0xFD=moving, 0xFE=open. WindowMotionFlags(B2): motion state bits. HIL-validated from Windows_cycle.log";
CM_ BO_ 953 "0x3B9 (Gate1): RR (passenger rear) Window position feedback. WindowPosition(B0): 0=closed to 87=fully open. WindowMovement(B1): 0xFC=closed, 0xFD=moving, 0xFE=open. WindowMotionFlags(B2): motion state bits. HIL-validated from Windows_cycle.log (no data on this HIL setup)";
CM_ BO_ 570 "0x23A (CAS): Keyfob / remote key action. Byte 1: 0x30=idle/key in, 0x33=key state. Byte 2: 0x00=none, 0x01=unlock, 0x04=lock, 0x10=boot unlock. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 586 "0x24A (PDC): Reverse gear status from FRM. Byte 0: 5=in reverse, 6=not in reverse; 2s period. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 594 "0x252 (Gate1): Wiper status. Byte 0: 0xCE=down/parked, 0xCD=going up. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 622 "0x26E (CAS): Rotary/iDrive encoder. Byte 2 RotaryAbsolute: 0-254 counts every notch regardless of direction. Byte 3 RotaryDirection: 0-254, up or down depending on rotation. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 714 "0x2CA (Kombi): Outside ambient temperature. Byte 0: (value-80)/2 = degC; byte 1=0xFF. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 725 "0x2D5 (Gate1): Rear window heater status. B0 bit0=RearWindowHeater (0xFC=off, 0xFD=on). Source: clima_modes_bottom_up.log HIL capture (ON at t=40.87s, OFF at t=43.87s)";
CM_ BO_ 726 "0x2D6 (Gate1): AC compressor valve status. Byte 1: 252=off, 253=on. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 742 "0x2E6 (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Climate air distribution — driver side (FA = Fahrerseite). B7=ClimateTemp actual driver zone output (raw/2 degC, e.g. 0x20=16C, 0x38=28C). B5=FanSpeed 1-7 (AUTO=0 not observed, min seen=1). B0/B1/B2=air distribution percentages for 3 vents: observed patterns: 0x28/0x32/0x64=default mix, 0x3C/0x64/0x00=floor-dominant, 0x2D/0x00/0x64=center-face, 0x00/0x3C/0x64=window mode, 0x64/0x00/0x00+B5=7=defrost, 0x00/0x64/0x00+B5=7=MAX AC. B3=0x29 constant. B6 bit6 set in MAX AC mode (0x7F vs 0x3F). Confirmed independent from passenger zone (0x2EA): driver stays fixed when only passenger zone adjusted. Source: clima_temp_fan.log + clima_modes_bottom_up.log HIL captures";
CM_ BO_ 746 "0x2EA (IHKA — Automatic Climate Control): Climate air distribution — passenger side (BF = Beifahrerseite). B7=ClimateTempPassenger actual passenger zone output (raw/2 degC, same scale as 0x2E6). Confirmed independent from driver zone: rises separately when only left/passenger knob is adjusted. Source: clima_temp_fan.log HIL capture";
CM_ BO_ 752 "0x2F0: [HYPOTHESIS — UNVERIFIED] Original DBC: Status_air_condition_functions, sender IHKA, 8 bytes. CONFLICT: 10minutes_run.log shows DLC=2, payload always F7 FC (100% static across 195 frames, period ~2000 ms, no variation during or after mirror adjustments). DBC DLC claim of 8 bytes does not match observed DLC=2. Copilot hypothesis: Mirror Status from TSG (door module) to FRM3 — bit0=MirrorMoveActive, bits1-2=MirrorMoveDirection, bit3=MirrorSelect, bit4=MirrorHeaterStatus, bit5=MirrorFault. This hypothesis is NOT supported by the drive log: payload never changes from F7 FC even when mirrors were physically adjusted. Static heartbeat behaviour is inconsistent with a movement-status frame. True identity unknown — needs HIL capture with known sender isolation.";
CM_ BO_ 753 "0x2F1: [HYPOTHESIS — UNVERIFIED] Original DBC: Status_driver_detection, sender MRSZ (occupant detection / airbag), 3 bytes — DLC matches observed DLC=3. 10minutes_run.log: 412 frames, period ~1000 ms. B0 and B1 are rolling counters (incrementing mod 256, loosely correlated). B2 alternates FC/FD. Rolling counter pattern is consistent with a periodic MRSZ heartbeat — NOT consistent with Copilot hypothesis of Mirror Command (button press bits from TSG). Copilot hypothesis claims bit0=AdjustUp, bit1=AdjustDown, bit2=AdjustLeft, bit3=AdjustRight, bit4=SelectLeft, bit5=SelectRight — payload structure (counter + counter + status nibble) does not match button-press bitmask semantics. Most likely this is genuine MRSZ occupant detection status. Needs HIL confirmation.";
CM_ SG_ 714 OutsideTemp "Byte 0: (raw-80)/2 = degC. Encoded as (degC*2)+80. DBC uses factor=0.5, offset=-40.";
CM_ SG_ 842 Longitude "32-bit signed raw. Decode: value / 11930464.71 - 360 = decimal degrees";
CM_ SG_ 842 Latitude "32-bit signed raw. Decode: value / 11930464.71 = decimal degrees";
CM_ SG_ 944 ReverseGear_3B0 "Byte 1: 0xFD=not in reverse, 0xFE=in reverse";
CM_ SG_ 586 ReverseGear_24A "Byte 0: 5=in reverse, 6=not in reverse";
CM_ BO_ 481 "0x1E1 (XXX): Counter and Door Status, sent every 200ms. Bytes 0-1 rolling counter (211-225 normal, 36-50/240-254 engine starting). Byte 2 door open bitmask: b0=driver, b2=passenger, b4=rear driver, b6=rear passenger. Bytes 3-5 padding 0xFF. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 631 "0x277 (iDrive controller): Reply to 0x273 (CCC/CIC). 4 bytes. Byte 3 bits 0-4 = screen number acknowledgement (TBC). Example: E1 9D 04 FF. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC";
CM_ BO_ 634 "0x27A: Navigation Graph Sync. Sender: CCC_GW (iDrive CCC Gateway). DLC 4. Source: rusefi.com BMW E65 Tool32 K-CAN table";
CM_ BO_ 840 "0x348: Navigation Graph Alignment. Sender: CCC_GW (iDrive CCC Gateway). DLC 4. Source: rusefi.com BMW E65 Tool32 K-CAN table";
CM_ BO_ 844 "0x34C: Navigation GPS 2. Sender: CCC_GW. DLC 5. Source: rusefi.com BMW E65 Tool32 K-CAN table";
CM_ BO_ 1009 "0x3F1: Extended Lighting Personalisation Status (CKM — Comfort Coding Module data). Sender: LM/FRM (Light Module / Footwell Module, node 0x70). Paired with 0x3F0 (Extended Lighting Personalisation Configuration from CCC_GW). Appears once at startup — FRM broadcasts current extended-lighting personalisation state. Source: MorGuux BMW E90 K-CAN gist (entry: 1009,0x3F1,Status Light Extended CKM [1],112,0x70,LM)";
CM_ BO_ 1043 "0x413: Unknown — 8-byte, ~1 s period. B2=0x97, B3=0x86, B6=0xE9, B7=0x87 are constant in all sessions; B0, B1, B4, B5 vary. Static (1 unique payload) in all focused HIL sessions (climate, gearbox, wipers). Highly variable (66+ unique payloads) in 5ninutes_Full_Run_Cycle.log (driving session) — no climate or gearbox correlation found. Likely a periodic counter or sensor broadcast from an unknown body module. Source: HIL sessions 2026-03-20";
CM_ BO_ 1045 "0x415: Unknown — 7-byte, ~1 s period. Static (1 unique payload) in all focused HIL sessions. Highly variable (82+ unique payloads) in 5ninutes_Full_Run_Cycle.log. Appears paired with 0x413 (adjacent IDs, same period). Likely config+status pair from the same unknown module. Source: HIL sessions 2026-03-20";
CM_ BO_ 1153 "0x481: BMW K-CAN Network Management alive frame — ACSM (Airbag Control Module, node 0x01). Source: MorGuux E90 K-CAN gist";
CM_ BO_ 1216 "0x4C0 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (52 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1238 "0x4D6 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (53 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1248 "0x4E0: BMW K-CAN Network Management alive frame — Kombi (instrument cluster, node 0x60). Source: MorGuux E90 K-CAN gist";
CM_ BO_ 1250 "0x4E2: BMW K-CAN Network Management alive frame — CCC_GW/M_ASK (iDrive CCC gateway, node 0x62). Source: MorGuux E90 K-CAN gist";
CM_ BO_ 1255 "0x4E7 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (55 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1266 "0x4F2 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (56 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1267 "0x4F3 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (56 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1272 "0x4F8 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Network Management alive message (51 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1409 "0x581: BMW K-CAN Services frame — ACSM (Airbag Control Module, node 0x01). Also carries seatbelt indicator: byte 3 bit 0 = 0x28=light off, 0x29=light on. Source: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC, MorGuux E90 K-CAN gist";
CM_ BO_ 1472 "0x5C0: BMW K-CAN Services frame — CAS (Car Access System, node 0x40). Source: MorGuux E90 K-CAN gist";
CM_ BO_ 1494 "0x5D6 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Services range message, rare (2 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1511 "0x5E7 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Services range message (22 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 1528 "0x5F8 (XXX): BMW K-CAN Services range message (11 frames); seen in t1.log";
CM_ BO_ 672 "CAS central locking. Two operating modes on same ID. (1) Periodic heartbeat (~5 s interval): B0=B1=B2=0x88 constant. B3: observed 0x00 at session start, flips to 0x01 within first 20s — purpose unknown, possibly CAS ready flag. B4-B7 encode lock state. Confirmed lock states across two sessions: UNLOCKED B5-B7=0x40 0x06 0x00, LOCKED B5-B7=0x43 0x1B 0x03. B4 is a ROLLING COUNTER — increments by 2 per heartbeat cycle (observed 0x20, 0x22, 0x24, 0x26, 0x28, 0x2A, 0x2C in 10minutes_run_Wheel_doors_tests.log 2026-03-24). The previous hypothesis that B4 encodes door-open flags (XOR=0x3C between sessions) was INCORRECT — the XOR difference was due to counter state difference between sessions, not door status. Per-door open status is carried in the individual door frames 0x0E2/0x0E6/0x0EA/0x0EE (B3: 0xFC=closed, 0xFD=open), not in 0x2A0. B3 (of 0x2A0) is a single bit flag (0x00 vs 0x01) observed toggling ~20s into the session — possible generic door-open indicator, needs further testing. Third state observed at t=580s after ignition off: 88 88 88 00 00 44 05 04 — likely deep standby/sleep entry (~240s after KL15 off). (2) Momentary command frame (single burst on key press, 3 rapid frames): B0=B1=0x11=unlock, 0x22=lock, 0x88=trunk-open. B2=0x18 observed with lock command while engine running (keyless-restart log 2026-03-24). B3=0x01 (same as heartbeat B3 state at time of command). Note: B2=0x18 vs previously-assumed 0x28 for lock — may depend on engine-running context. LOCK-RUNNING-CAR CONFIRMED: 0x2A0 B0=B1=0x22 command burst observed at t+33s in keyless-restart scenario (driver locked running car from outside with keyfob) — all door frames simultaneously transition B0 from 0x81→0x82 (unlocked→locked). Source: idCanSend.txt + 10minutes_run.log 2026-03-22 + HIL 2026-03-23 + keyless-restart 2026-03-24";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockCmd_B0 "Command type byte in momentary key-press frame. 0x11=Unlock, 0x22=Lock, 0x88=TrunkOpen. In periodic heartbeat frames this byte is always 0x88 regardless of lock state. Always identical to LockCmd_B1.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockCmd_B1 "Mirror of LockCmd_B0 in command frames. In periodic heartbeat frames always 0x88.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockCmd_B2 "Byte 2. In command frames (empirical bench): 0x18 with Unlock, 0x28 with Lock, 0x80 with TrunkOpen. In periodic heartbeat frames always 0x88.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockState_B3 "Always 0x01 in both unlocked and locked heartbeat captures. Purpose unknown.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockState_B4 "Lock state byte 4. Heartbeat: 0x06=unlocked, 0x08=locked (confirmed from drive log auto-lock at 5 km/h). Bit encoding unknown — HIL LOCK-01 required.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockState_B5 "Lock state byte 5. Heartbeat: 0x40=unlocked, 0x43=locked. Bit encoding unknown — HIL LOCK-01 required.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockState_B6 "Lock state byte 6. Heartbeat: 0x06=unlocked, 0x1B=locked. Bit encoding unknown — HIL LOCK-01 required.";
CM_ SG_ 672 LockState_B7 "Lock state byte 7. Heartbeat: 0x00=unlocked, 0x03=locked. Bit encoding unknown — HIL LOCK-01 required.";
CM_ BO_ 1987 "0x7C3: CAS Application Message 2. Sender: CAS (Car Access System) / end-of-line calibration tool. Trace DLC=8 (E65 table says DLC=3, loopybunny says DLC=8 — 8 retained from trace). Keyfob security, comfort and CBS (Condition Based Service) data; byte 0 always 0xE2 in t1.log. Sources: loopybunny.co.uk/CarPC, rusefi.com BMW E65 Tool32 K-CAN table";

